{
  "texts": [
    "It is important to remember the material flows of electricity, water, air, heat, metals, minerals, and rare earth elements that undergird these technologies (Monserrate, 2022).",
    "Data centers, with their dependency on cool air and infrastructure, take up important resources like space (Solon, 2021), water (Ion, 2021), and electricity (Jones, 2018).",
    "One of the most energy-intensive activities is machine learning (Hao, 2019).",
    "Additionally, data centers are loud.",
    "They are common culprits for noise pollution given their intensive cooling needs."
  ]
}